{"word":"ρεῦμα","slug":"ρεῦμα","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ρεῦμα</b></el> <el>(ρεῦμα, ατος, τό,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:ρέω'><el>ρέω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>that which flows, a flow, stream, current</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>the stream</i> of a river, mostly in <a href='S:plural'>pl.</a>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>; <i>a stream of lava</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>: <a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>a stream</i> or <i>flood of men</i>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>a flood</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>a discharge</i> from the body, <i>a flux, rheum</i>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}